:false,"topic_id":493857,"topic_slug":"on-the-fly-path-planner-short-distances","display_username":"icemannie","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/pathplanners-pathfinding-not-working-for-close-pose-estimation/484786","internal":true,"reflection":false,"title":"Pathplanner's pathfinding not working for close pose estimation","clicks":76}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":28240,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/on-the-fly-path-planner-short-distances/493857/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3544937,"name":"","username":"RoyalKnight","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/ce7236/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-02T17:38:24.131Z","cooked":"<p>Thanks for the response! I’m a little confused… What’s the difference between on the fly paths and pathfinding?</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":16,"updated_at":"2025-03-02T17:38:24.131Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":229,"readers_count":228,"score":65.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":493857,"topic_slug":"on-the-fly-path-planner-short-distances","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":28240,"username":"icemannie","name":"icemannie","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/i/bc79bd/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":65426,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/on-the-fly-path-planner-short-distances/493857/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3544941,"name":"","username":"TheBatman","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/thebatman/{size}/255139_2.png","created_at":"2025-03-02T17:53:07.811Z","cooked":"<p>Pathfinding is when you use the PathplannerLibs pathFind method, if you are generating a path in the following way than it is on-the-fly path generating and not path finding:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">List&lt;Waypoint&gt; waypoints = PathPlannerPath.waypointsFromPoses(
        new Pose2d(1.0, 1.0, Rotation2d.fromDegrees(0)),
        new Pose2d(3.0, 1.0, Rotation2d.fromDegrees(0)),
        new Pose2d(5.0, 3.0, Rotation2d.fromDegrees(90))
);

PathConstraints constraints = new PathConstraints(3.0, 3.0, 2 * Math.PI, 4 * Math.PI); // The constraints for this path.
// PathConstraints constraints = PathConstraints.unlimitedConstraints(12.0); // You can also use unlimited constraints, only limited by motor torque and nominal battery voltage

// Create the path using the waypoints created above
PathPlannerPath path = new PathPlannerPath(
        waypoints,
        constraints,
        null, // The ideal starting state, this is only relevant for pre-planned paths, so can be null for on-the-fly paths.
        new GoalEndState(0.0, Rotation2d.fromDegrees(-90)) // Goal end state. You can set a holonomic rotation here. If using a differential drivetrain, the rotation will have no effect.
);
</code></pre>
<p>Here is pathfinding code for contrast:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">Pose2d targetPose = new Pose2d(10, 5, Rotation2d.fromDegrees(180));

// Create the constraints to use while pathfinding
PathConstraints constraints = new PathConstraints(
        3.0, 4.0,
        Units.degreesToRadians(540), Units.degreesToRadians(720));

// Since AutoBuilder is configured, we can use it to build pathfinding commands
Command pathfindingCommand = AutoBuilder.pathfindToPose(
        targetPose,
        constraints,
        0.0, // Goal end velocity in meters/sec
        0.0 // Rotation delay distance in meters. This is how far the robot should travel before attempting to rotate.
);
</code></pre>
<p>The difference is that pathfinding is less controlled - it will generate the fasted path from point A to point B with consideration to the field - but you cannot control it’s end rotation - because of that pathfinding isn’t recommended for alignment but for reaching a point from where a pre-generated path is called for the final alignment.</p>
<p>On-the-fly path generating can struggle in short distance due to the nature of path generation, when you generate a path it will create a trajectory with considerations for angle of movement in the waypoints provided and often generating a trajectory for small distances is just impossible - you might be able to play a little with angles of movement to make it do a straight line but it might not help much.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":16,"updated_at":"2025-03-02T17:53:07.811Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":9,"reads":213,"readers_count":212,"score":107.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":493857,"topic_slug":"on-the-fly-path-planner-short-distances","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":65426,"username":"RoyalKnight","name":"","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/ce7236/{size}.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":71857,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"Vigilante"},"post_url":"/t/on-the-fly-path-planner-short-distances/493857/4","custom_user_title":"Vigilante","reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3545063,"name":"","username":"RoyalKnight","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/ce7236/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-03-02T21:07:49.570Z","cooked":"<p>Makes total 